Subject: Publish docker image to ghcr.io/nadicodeai/nadia

Replace upstream's Docker Hub publish flow with a GitHub Container
Registry publish so the image lands at ghcr.io/nadicodeai/nadia. The
nadicodeai org does not own a Docker Hub namespace, and the upstream
workflow's `secrets.DOCKERHUB_USERNAME` / `DOCKERHUB_TOKEN` secrets
are not configured in this repo.

Why the image name is `nadia`, not `nadia-agent`: this pristine-fork repo
(nadicodeai/argo) publishes a `nadia` image. The legacy in-tree rename repo
(nadicodeai/nadia-agent) used `…/nadia-agent` because that GitHub repo was
named that way. We do not carry that legacy image name forward — see
.shepherd/spec.md § Project Structure.

Auth uses the workflow's built-in GITHUB_TOKEN with `packages: write`,
so no secret setup is required. All three `docker/login-action` steps
in the current upstream workflow (build-amd64, build-arm64, merge) are
flipped from the DOCKERHUB_* secrets to `registry: ghcr.io` +
`github.actor` / `secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN`, and the `IMAGE_NAME` env var
carries the new value. The `packages: write` permission is added.

(Note: upstream's docker-publish.yml has since collapsed the old
move-latest job and the inline `image=nousresearch/hermes-agent`
ancestor-check shell vars into the merge job's `${IMAGE_NAME}`
references, so there is nothing else to rebrand here; the assertions
in patches/asserts/0005 pin the GHCR end-state.)

Note: the four `if: github.repository == 'NousResearch/hermes-agent'`
guards are intentionally not touched by this patch. The rename engine
maps `NousResearch/hermes-agent` → `nadicodeai/argo`, so they end up
correct in `dist/nadia/` automatically.

Spec FR-7 (Docker image), FR-11 (Docker-only distribution).

Index: .sync-workdir/.github/workflows/docker-publish.yml
